      <p>
        <s>In his text <ref target="c10gk5_1" type="title">Hope of escape lost in translation</ref> published at the <date>17th December 2016</date> in <name type="misc">The Sunday Times</name> the author <ref target="c10gk5_1" type="author">Zia Haider Rahman</ref> tells us about his view on language learning.</s>
        <s>He says that we should stop using translation and interpreting, services and start to learn <choice><orig>english</orig><reg>English</reg></choice> <ref target="c10gk5_1" type="line">(ll. 20-21)</ref>.</s>
        <s>Furthermore he says that immigrants should learn <quote>to stand on their own feet</quote> and to speak <choice><orig>english</orig><reg>English</reg></choice>, because there are many advantages when anyone can speak <choice><orig>english</orig><reg>English</reg></choice> <ref target="c10gk5_1" type="line">(ll. 18, 23)</ref>.</s>
      </p>
